We all like sheep have gone astray.

25:59.871 --> 26:07.743
Each of us has turned our own way, and the Lord has laid on him the iniquity of us all.

26:10.066 --> 26:13.992
He was oppressed and afflicted, yet he did not open his mouth.

26:15.374 --> 26:20.882
By oppression and judgment he was taken away, yet who of his generation protested?

26:22.882 --> 26:27.388
He was cut off from the land of the living for the transgression of my people.

26:27.808 --> 26:28.609
He was punished.

26:30.792 --> 26:39.844
He was assigned a grave with the wicked and with the rich in his death, though he had done no violence, nor was there any deceit in his mouth.

26:41.647 --> 26:46.052
Yet it was the Lord's will to crush him and cause him to suffer.

26:47.755 --> 26:50.418
And though the Lord makes his life an offering for sin,

26:51.010 --> 26:56.698
He will see his offspring and prolong his days, and the will of the Lord will prosper in his hand.

26:58.280 --> 27:03.707
After he had suffered, he will see the light of life and be satisfied.

27:04.488 --> 27:11.658
By his knowledge, my righteous servant will justify many, and he will bear their iniquities.

27:13.020 --> 27:20.370
Therefore, I have given him a portion among the great, and he will divide the spoils with the strong.

27:21.410 --> 27:32.781
because he poured his life out unto death and was numbered with the transgressors, for he bore the Son of many and made intercession for the transgressors.

27:34.443 --> 27:42.550
A bit later on it says, for a brief moment I abandoned you, but with deep compassion I will bring you back.

27:43.852 --> 27:50.578
In a surge of anger I hid my face from you, for a moment, but with everlasting kindness,

27:50.722 --> 27:53.825
I will have compassion on you," says the Lord, your Redeemer.

27:55.346 --> 27:57.428
To me, this is like the days of Noah.

27:58.229 --> 28:01.733
When I swore that the waters of Noah will never again cover the earth.

28:02.714 --> 28:08.339
So now I have sworn again not to be angry with you, never to rebuke you again.

28:08.379 --> 28:15.646
Though the mountains be shaken and the hills be removed, yet my unfailing love for you will not be shaken.

28:15.666 --> 28:19.730
Nor my covenant of peace be removed, says the Lord.

28:20.066 --> 28:22.428
who has compassion on you.

28:26.653 --> 28:28.535
That was Isaiah 53 and 54.

28:33.720 --> 28:34.861
The ultimate price.

28:36.623 --> 28:38.725
He has redeemed us.

28:46.173 --> 28:47.634
But he didn't stay dead.

28:52.354 --> 28:54.256
God himself is a source of life.

28:55.958 --> 28:57.620
Death has no hold on him.

28:58.581 --> 29:05.869
And in the same way, because we are no longer slaves to sin, death has no hold on you.

29:11.495 --> 29:17.362
Romans 6, verse 5 to 7 says, for we have been united with him in a death like his,

29:17.506 --> 29:22.852
we will certainly also be united with him in a resurrection like his.

29:24.334 --> 29:38.490
For we know that our old self was crucified with him so that the body ruled by sin might be done away with, that we should no longer be slaves to sin because anyone who has died has been set free from sin.

29:42.314 --> 29:45.778
He has plugged us in again to the source of life.

29:49.922 --> 29:54.106
And the source of life is the God who loves us.

29:58.070 --> 29:59.711
So I'm just going to pause and pray for a moment.

30:01.293 --> 30:04.296
Thank you, Lord Jesus, for what you've done.

30:04.336 --> 30:13.044
And we come to you, Lord, knowing that it wasn't anything we could do.

30:14.845 --> 30:19.730
And that in fact, we've messed up most of the time and that we've been slaves to sin.

30:22.114 --> 30:39.694
Forgive us, Lord, in your great mercy, and pull us from death to life by the power of your blood and your infinite kindness.

30:41.876 --> 30:43.198
In Jesus' name, amen.

30:45.701 --> 30:46.962
So now I was asking you

30:48.642 --> 30:52.706
when we've been thinking about these things, to ask the main questions, the big questions.

30:54.909 --> 30:55.870
How do I see myself?

30:56.731 --> 30:57.892
How do I relate to God?

30:58.593 --> 30:59.954
And how do I live day by day?

31:04.940 --> 31:07.283
And in some sense, those are questions for you to answer.

31:08.864 --> 31:09.825
But may I just give you this?

31:11.908 --> 31:17.714
When you see yourself, do you see someone who is loved

31:18.242 --> 31:20.024
more than you could possibly imagine.

31:24.708 --> 31:30.133
And when you relate to the Lord God, he is your father who loves you.

31:32.936 --> 31:47.410
And he made a way so that even though you were enemies with him, you were subject to death, you can now come because that veil is torn and we can boldly

31:47.650 --> 31:49.252
Approach the throne of grace.

31:54.316 --> 31:55.578
And how do we live day by day?

31:58.200 --> 31:59.301
It really is this simple.

32:03.045 --> 32:04.687
Unite yourself with Jesus.

32:05.888 --> 32:07.169
Abide in Him.

32:07.229 --> 32:16.498
Because when you're united with Him, you are pulled from death to life, plugged into the source of life

32:17.186 --> 32:19.509
and then you're able to love.

32:21.592 --> 32:25.557
The love that God has for you, you're able to love others.

32:33.487 --> 32:34.108
This is love.

32:34.949 --> 32:40.576
Not that we loved God, but that he loved us and sent his son as an atoning sacrifice for our sins.

32:41.257 --> 32:45.362
Dear friends, God so loved us

32:45.730 --> 32:48.514
Since God so loved us, we also ought to love one another.

32:49.556 --> 32:56.466
No one has ever seen God, but if we love one another, God lives in us and his love is made complete in us.

32:57.127 --> 33:00.432
This is how we know that we live in him and he and us.

33:01.053 --> 33:02.936
He has given us his spirit.

33:05.961 --> 33:12.050
Now that one final thought, and if you would just extend a little bit more time,

33:14.882 --> 33:22.011
And sometimes we think when we pray the prayer for the Lord Jesus to come into our hearts, we will be changed.

33:24.494 --> 33:28.098
And that is true, but we're an impatient society.

33:29.660 --> 33:31.602
We think the change will be instantaneous.

33:32.283 --> 33:44.658
And the image I've got in my mind is, do you not boot in the beast, that old cartoon where you've got the beast, the epitome of selfishness and malice, and suddenly

33:44.770 --> 33:45.832
He encounters love.

33:46.893 --> 33:53.643
Somebody says that she loves him and the magic rain and the swirling clothes.

33:53.663 --> 33:56.047
And it's a wonderfully exciting moment in the movie.

33:57.589 --> 33:58.410
And he's changed.

34:00.053 --> 34:00.834
I love the way you laugh at me.

34:00.854 --> 34:01.174
It's great.

34:03.037 --> 34:04.880
He changes from a beast to a prince.

34:07.804 --> 34:09.627
And in some sense, Jesus does do that.

34:10.128 --> 34:14.514
He takes our beast like hearts and he makes us royalty.

34:14.882 --> 34:15.703
children of the king.

34:16.744 --> 34:18.726
We're changed from the beast to the prince.

34:20.227 --> 34:22.229
But it doesn't necessarily happen.

34:24.071 --> 34:24.932
Bang, like that.

34:27.875 --> 34:30.458
It's more like, got this picture here.

34:30.478 --> 34:31.479
I don't know if you can see it.

34:31.899 --> 34:34.982
It's a tree growing out of a rock.

34:38.426 --> 34:40.508
God plants his seed in us.

34:41.108 --> 34:42.930
The power over

34:43.362 --> 34:45.665
that that raised crash from the dead is in you.

34:48.267 --> 34:50.910
But it grows in kind of a slow way.

34:53.613 --> 35:01.062
The thing is, even in slow growth, it's still powerful enough to split the rock apart.

35:04.005 --> 35:04.886
So be encouraged.

35:07.589 --> 35:12.114
One two Peter three says, but we do not forget this one thing, dear friends.

35:12.770 --> 35:17.618
With the Lord, a day is like a thousand years and a thousand years is like a day.

35:18.920 --> 35:24.389
The Lord is not slow in keeping His promise as some understand slowness.

35:25.411 --> 35:32.562
Instead, He is patient with you, not wanting anyone to perish, but everyone to come to repentance.

35:34.506 --> 35:37.170
But the day of the Lord will come like a thief.

35:38.690 --> 35:44.297
The heavens will disappear with a roar, the elements will be destroyed by fire, and the earth and everything in it will be laid bare.

35:45.118 --> 35:48.963
Since everything will be destroyed in this way, what kind of people ought we to be?

35:49.804 --> 35:56.912
You ought to live holy and godly lies as you look forward to the day of God and speed it's coming.

35:59.696 --> 36:02.199
So magical transformation might come.

36:03.500 --> 36:08.146
And we look forward to that day when these bodies that are subject to death

36:08.354 --> 36:09.155
are done away with.

36:10.516 --> 36:28.936
But until then, you've got the power of God inside you, inside your very heart, to bring love and light into the darkness of this world, because He is wanting everyone to be reconciled to Him.

36:30.158 --> 36:37.906
So friends, be changed by this truth that God demonstrated His love

36:38.402 --> 36:44.352
In this, while we were still sinners, Christ died for us.

36:45.974 --> 36:51.102
Thank you, Lord God, for just how much you love us.

36:52.344 --> 37:05.906
Help us, Lord, to unite with you, to be changed, to be more like you, Lord Jesus, so that we might love those who are lost the same way you love us.

37:07.042 --> 37:21.026
and may your kingdom come, and your will be done in our hearts and in the spaces we inhabit, by the mighty power of your name in your mighty name, Jesus.

37:21.046 --> 37:22.589
We've come to the end of this week's message.

37:23.190 --> 37:24.853
We hope you've been impacted and inspired.

37:25.654 --> 37:32.466
Please keep up to date with everything that's happening by visiting our websites at www.livechurchwarrington.com.

